From aebd4142974db91a972ad5f2c1e7b13a48a8a1e1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Philipp Grulich <philippgrulich@hotmail.de>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 12:46:17 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Add val<StructType> support with stack allocation, field
 access, and copy semantics

Introduces AllocaOperation for stack-allocated struct values, extends tracing and
all backends (MLIR, C++, BC) to handle struct construction, field get/set, copy
construction/assignment, and destructors. Adds val_std.hpp with higher-level
struct wrappers and comprehensive tests covering construction, mutation, loops,
and non-trivial types.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
